      "writtenOn": "2020-06-24T20:35:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "preexisting nit, not asking for any change in this CL:\n\nShould we document in SkColorFilter.h that new flags (if any) need to make sense if they are bit-anded together? We also a follow similar pattern for the optimization-flags in GrFragmentProcessors, and it works well there, but I can imagine someone adding a new flag to SkColorFilter in a future CL without realizing that the same pattern applies here.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 117,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 118,
        "endChar": 59
      },
      "revId": "e477efcc6d0eff19d3b007c36c6e2fbc14dcd051",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "879f98ea_9dde236f",
        "filename": "src/core/SkColorFilter.cpp",
